The paper deals with low-level vision problems such as high dynamic range imaging, motion edge detection, photometric stereo, image alignment, and recovery. These problems are typically associated with computer vision and image processing, which fall under the category of computer science (cs). The paper proposes a new approach to Robust Principal Component Analysis (RPCA) via rank minimization, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.IT). The proposed approach involves minimizing the partial sum of singular values, which is a numerical optimization problem that can be solved using numerical analysis techniques (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents experimental results that demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which is a common practice in applied machine learning and computer vision research (cs.SI).
